ProMED from HealthMap Alerts

[For a discussion of syphilis in the United States, please see my moderator comments in prior posts listed in the "See Also" section below.

We are not told in the news report above the characteristics of the population infected with syphilis or factors that are placing them at risk of infection in Escambia County, Florida. More information would be appreciated from knowledgeable sources.

In the late 1980s, in Escambia County, Florida, the number of early syphilis cases reported per quarter increased from 15 in 1987 to 75 in 1990 (https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/00001989.htm). The outbreak was linked to use of crack cocaine, multiple anonymous sex partners, and exchange of sex for money or drugs.

In recent ProMED posts, illicit drug use has been cited as a contributing factor for increases in syphilis cases in both the United States and Canada (see the "See Also" section below). Illicit drug use is associated with sexual behaviors that increase the risk for acquiring syphilis and other sexually transmitted diseases, including having multiple anonymous sex partners, inconsistent condom use, and exchange of sex for drugs or money.

In my moderator comments in prior ProMED posts on syphilis in the USA, I noted that Florida was one of the states in which the rate of congenital syphilis (64.8 per 100 000) was above the national average (48.5 cases per 100 000) in 2019 (see Table 40, https://www.cdc.gov/std/statistics/2019/tables/40.htm).

Escambia County (pop., 297 619 in 2010) is the westernmost county in the US state of Florida. It is in the state's northwestern corner (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Escambia_County,_Florida); its largest city and county seat is Pensacola (est. pop. 52 975 residents in 2019) (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pensacola,_Florida). Escambia County is home to a large United States Naval Air Station, the base of the Blue Angels, a flight demonstration team of the US Navy, and the National Naval Aviation Museum. A map showing the location of Escambia County can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Escambia+County,+FL. - Mod.ML

